Discussion.S:
A projection to the ventral premammillary nucleus has 
    been reported (Krettek and Price, 1978a; Post and Mai, 1980; 
    Kevetter and Winans, 1981; Luiten et al., 1985; Caffe et al., 1987; 
    Gomez and Newman, 1992), and our work indicates that the MEApd 
    supplies the most fibers.

Targets of MEA projections that are clearly part of this 
    sexually dimorphic circuit include the accessory olfactory bulb; 
    principal nucleus of the BST and ventral lateral septa1 nucleus; 
    and medial preoptic, anteroventral periventricular, ventromedial, 
    and ventral premammillary nuclei.
